273
00:08:59,654 --> 00:09:02,052
Since Soo Geun is upset,

274
00:09:02,053 --> 00:09:04,452
I'll deliver it to you in an entertaining way.

275
00:09:04,453 --> 00:09:06,862
- Nice.
- I don't even remember your rank...

276
00:09:06,863 --> 00:09:07,892
when I came in first.

277
00:09:07,893 --> 00:09:09,362
I don't remember that either. I'm sorry.

278
00:09:09,363 --> 00:09:10,363
They're even now.

279
00:09:10,364 --> 00:09:11,632
- I'll begin.
- Okay.

280
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,132
- Respond enthusiastically.
- Okay.

281
00:09:13,133 --> 00:09:14,633
- Ready. Get set. Go.
- Ready. Get set. Go.

282
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:17,102
- What?
- She's tap dancing.

283
00:09:17,103 --> 00:09:18,172
She's tap dancing.

284
00:09:18,173 --> 00:09:19,173
- Go.
- Go.

285
00:09:19,174 --> 00:09:20,972
(Tap dancing)

286
00:09:20,973 --> 00:09:23,142
- She's tap dancing.
- She's tap dancing.

287
00:09:23,143 --> 00:09:24,443
(You just can't take your eyes off her dazzling dance moves.)

288
00:09:24,973 --> 00:09:26,343
- You're doing great.
- Oh, my.

289
00:09:27,413 --> 00:09:28,712
- How do you do that?
- Wait for a moment.

290
00:09:28,713 --> 00:09:29,713
Look at her legs.

291
00:09:29,714 --> 00:09:31,653
(The bounce is spreading as if it were contagious.)

292
00:09:32,123 --> 00:09:34,153
(She's shaking her foot like crazy, just like a thresher.)

293
00:09:34,483 --> 00:09:35,653
(Opening up her backpack)

294
00:09:35,993 --> 00:09:38,623
(It's time for the long-awaited finale.)

295
00:09:39,693 --> 00:09:41,262
(She put on a beautiful performance while handing out the document.)

296
00:09:41,263 --> 00:09:43,162
- She wrapped it up nicely.
- Her tap dancing was great.

297
00:09:43,163 --> 00:09:44,263
- Nice!
- Great job!

298
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:46,832
- She's so great at tap dancing.
- Tap dancing is hard.

299
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:48,602
- Yoo Jung, did you learn that?
- Did you learn how to tap dance?

300
00:09:48,603 --> 00:09:51,033
For the role I played in a musical,

301
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:53,402
- I learned tap dancing last year.
- You see...

302
00:09:53,403 --> 00:09:54,972
- For a year...
- How long did you practice?

303
00:09:54,973 --> 00:09:58,642
Including the performance period, I spent almost a year practicing.

304
00:09:58,643 --> 00:10:00,612
- That's right.
- When D.O. came on this show,

305
00:10:00,613 --> 00:10:01,782
he showcased his tap dancing skills.

306
00:10:01,783 --> 00:10:02,852
- Yes, that's right.
- D.O. tap danced here as well.

307
00:10:02,853 --> 00:10:04,612
- D.O. of EXO tap danced here.
- So you did it in your movie?

308
00:10:04,613 --> 00:10:06,882
- Last year, Yoo Jung...
- Oh, really?

309
00:10:06,883 --> 00:10:10,152
played Peggy Sawyer in "42nd Street."

310
00:10:10,153 --> 00:10:11,322
- Really?
- Yes.

311
00:10:11,323 --> 00:10:13,192
- Yes, it was my first time...
- Peggy Sawyer.

312
00:10:13,193 --> 00:10:14,592
- playing a lead role.
- Oh, I see.

313
00:10:14,593 --> 00:10:16,333
- I heard she did a great job.
- She really did a great job.

314
00:10:16,363 --> 00:10:18,232
- Right. She did a wonderful job.
- She was amazing.

315
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:20,603
She's still so light on her feet, even after ten years.

316
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:22,772
Indeed. She was very young back then.

317
00:10:22,773 --> 00:10:24,032
- She's at an age where people...
- Right.

318
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:25,772
- reach their physical peak.
- That's right.

319
00:10:25,773 --> 00:10:27,142
- Really?
- We're still young.

320
00:10:27,143 --> 00:10:28,343
- Is that true?
- Yes.

321
00:10:29,143 --> 00:10:30,842
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

322
00:10:30,843 --> 00:10:32,742
Names, Lim Na Young, Chungha, Kim So Hye,

323
00:10:32,743 --> 00:10:34,743
Yoo Yeon Jung, Choi Yoo Jung, Kim Do Yeon, Jeon So Mi.

324
00:10:35,683 --> 00:10:38,583
They've returned to this school. Let's check out their transfer form.

325
00:10:39,153 --> 00:10:41,583
The first thing to check out is...

326
00:10:42,223 --> 00:10:45,422
their nicknames, and they wrote "new" next to "nicknames."

327
00:10:45,423 --> 00:10:48,992
- It means they got new nicknames.
- Because ten years have passed.

328
00:10:48,993 --> 00:10:51,293
- Because ten years have passed?
- We wrote our new nicknames.

329
00:10:51,493 --> 00:10:54,033
First, Na Young's nickname is Little Mermaid.

330
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:56,002
- Next.
- Let me explain.

331
00:10:56,003 --> 00:10:58,802
There's a chat room with our staff in it.

332
00:10:58,803 --> 00:11:01,403
Since I barely said anything in that chat room...

333
00:11:02,443 --> 00:11:03,872
- You see...
- As if you lost your voice?

334
00:11:03,873 --> 00:11:06,412
- The mermaid who lost her voice...
- Let me explain about her nickname.

335
00:11:06,413 --> 00:11:08,242
We began talking about our reunion last year...

336
00:11:08,243 --> 00:11:11,513
since this year marks our tenth anniversary.

337
00:11:11,653 --> 00:11:15,183
Na Young is usually quiet...

338
00:11:15,893 --> 00:11:17,223
- and doesn't show much emotion.
- She's quiet.

339
00:11:17,323 --> 00:11:19,762
And she was even quieter than usual when we gathered.

340
00:11:19,763 --> 00:11:22,263
Someone asked her if she had anything to say.

341
00:11:22,663 --> 00:11:25,663
With an expressionless face, she just said, "Sounds good."

342
00:11:25,803 --> 00:11:27,732
Did you stay quiet to save your voice?

343
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,402
- No, that's not the case.
- Were you preparing for a concert?

344
00:11:29,403 --> 00:11:33,373
I just liked listening to everyone's thoughts,

345
00:11:33,543 --> 00:11:36,412
and they came up with so many great ideas.

346
00:11:36,413 --> 00:11:37,872
- So I didn't have anything to say.
- You didn't have anything to say.

347
00:11:37,873 --> 00:11:39,283
- You didn't want to talk to them.
- No.

348
00:11:39,783 --> 00:11:42,652
She neither agreed nor disagreed. She didn't say a word.

349
00:11:42,653 --> 00:11:45,283
- Really?
- When we had a meeting,

350
00:11:45,553 --> 00:11:47,452
I thought Na Young didn't show up until the end of the meeting.

351
00:11:47,453 --> 00:11:50,592
- When it ended, I finally saw her.
- She was there?

352
00:11:50,593 --> 00:11:51,892
Is she a ghost or what?

353
00:11:51,893 --> 00:11:53,962
- Exactly. She's like a ghost.
- I always...

354
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:56,992
- observe them from the sidelines.
- As if she meditated silently.

355
00:11:56,993 --> 00:11:58,362
- You're considerate of them.
- Isn't that right?

356
00:11:58,363 --> 00:12:00,162
That's why she used to be called Stone Na Young.

357
00:12:00,163 --> 00:12:02,372
- Yes, that's right.
- When she was here ten years ago,

358
00:12:02,373 --> 00:12:04,572
her expression never changed whether she was happy or sad.

359
00:12:04,573 --> 00:12:05,642
- Right.
- That's why...

360
00:12:05,643 --> 00:12:06,672
she was called Stone Na Young.

361
00:12:06,673 --> 00:12:07,872
- That's right.
- That's right.

362
00:12:07,873 --> 00:12:09,972
- You remember that?
- Don't let him fool you.

363
00:12:09,973 --> 00:12:13,013
- He takes lessons before our shoot.
- One-on-one lessons.

364
00:12:13,443 --> 00:12:14,582
- One-on-one lessons.
- So he learns by rote.

365
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:15,982
- He crams...
- Like personal fitness training.

366
00:12:15,983 --> 00:12:18,552
- He takes private lessons.
- like students do for an exam.

367
00:12:18,553 --> 00:12:20,623
While eating naengmyeon, he'd mutter, "April, Stone Na Young."

368
00:12:21,023 --> 00:12:22,552
"April, Stone Na Young."

369
00:12:22,553 --> 00:12:24,923
"April, Stone Na Young." He memorizes the info like that.

370
00:12:25,493 --> 00:12:27,023
"April, Stone Na Young."

371
00:12:27,823 --> 00:12:29,793
- "That was her nickname."
- I'm curious about something.

372
00:12:29,993 --> 00:12:31,292
- She's curious about something.
- Go ahead and ask us.

373
00:12:31,293 --> 00:12:34,562
- I want to hear Sang Min's voice.
- That's what he always does.

374
00:12:34,563 --> 00:12:36,533
Sang Min is the Little Mermaid of this show.

375
00:12:36,703 --> 00:12:38,772
- He's our Little Mermaid.
- He's our Little Mermaid.

376
00:12:38,773 --> 00:12:39,942
No wonder...

377
00:12:39,943 --> 00:12:41,142
- Na Young, you're Little Mermaid...
- I mean...

378
00:12:41,143 --> 00:12:44,612
- We met him on a show yesterday.
- Really?

379
00:12:44,613 --> 00:12:47,813
- "Uh, But Like, Seriously?"
- He's her ideal type.

380
00:12:48,283 --> 00:12:50,782
- That's why...
- He's wild on that show.

381
00:12:50,783 --> 00:12:52,682
- He's one of the hosts of the show.
- I can't even see him clearly.

382
00:12:52,683 --> 00:12:53,983
He's even invisible.

383
00:12:54,183 --> 00:12:55,752
- Ho Dong completely blocks him...
- Did you guys...

384
00:12:55,753 --> 00:12:57,323
from our sight.

385
00:12:58,253 --> 00:12:59,622
- He's invisible because of Ho Dong.
- It was first time seeing him.

386
00:12:59,623 --> 00:13:01,822
