404
00:13:36,763 --> 00:13:39,503
She reacts like this. "Exactly. That's right. Yes."

405
00:13:40,033 --> 00:13:41,132
"Yes, girl."

406
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:43,232
- Does she react right away?
- "Okay." She reacts like this.

407
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:44,503
I guess she reacts with a lot of filler words,

408
00:13:44,703 --> 00:13:47,073
making it enjoyable to talk to her.

409
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:49,443
- She's good with filler words.
- It must be enjoyable.

410
00:13:49,573 --> 00:13:51,213
- Her reactions are so cute.
- Indeed.

411
00:13:52,013 --> 00:13:54,513
- That's why I got the nickname.
- React-Chungha. I see.

412
00:13:54,713 --> 00:13:57,853
(Let's check out React-Chungha's reaction moments.)

413
00:13:58,213 --> 00:13:59,352
(Patting)

414
00:13:59,353 --> 00:14:00,523
(She's cute.)

415
00:14:00,753 --> 00:14:02,153
(Oh, really?)

416
00:14:02,993 --> 00:14:04,392
Let me explain.

417
00:14:04,393 --> 00:14:05,422
(Even while drinking water...)

418
00:14:05,423 --> 00:14:07,523
(She reacted enthusiastically.)

419
00:14:08,193 --> 00:14:10,392
(The reaction fairy of I.O.I)

420
00:14:10,393 --> 00:14:11,832
What was your old nickname?

421
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,562
I used to be called Dance President.

422
00:14:13,563 --> 00:14:14,732
- Dance President.
- Oh, Dance President?

423
00:14:14,733 --> 00:14:17,132
- She told us that earlier.
- She had several nicknames.

424
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:18,803
- She said it was her nickname.
- Dance President.

425
00:14:18,973 --> 00:14:20,802
Oh, there's one more. It's Granny Chung.

426
00:14:20,803 --> 00:14:22,543
- Right, Granny Chung.
- She used to be called that too.

427
00:14:22,813 --> 00:14:23,913
Granny Chung?

428
00:14:24,273 --> 00:14:25,682
- He...
- Why would he get mad at me?

429
00:14:25,683 --> 00:14:27,383
He doesn't even know anything.

430
00:14:27,713 --> 00:14:29,683
Don't get mad if you're not sure.

431
00:14:30,183 --> 00:14:31,983
- Ho Dong.
- She had two nicknames.

432
00:14:32,113 --> 00:14:34,453
- Ho Dong.
- Dance President and Granny Chung.

433
00:14:35,123 --> 00:14:36,993
- I remember "Granny Chung."
- I used to be called Granny Chung.

434
00:14:37,123 --> 00:14:39,822
When we worked together ten years ago,

435
00:14:39,823 --> 00:14:42,222
- I appeared on many dance shows.
- That's right.

436
00:14:42,223 --> 00:14:44,932
The only time I could practice was late at night.

437
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:47,502
- So I dozed off during the day.
- She always dozed off.

438
00:14:47,503 --> 00:14:50,432
Or I'd just sit in a corner, completely exhausted.

439
00:14:50,433 --> 00:14:52,342
- That's why you were called Granny.
- That's how I got the nickname.

440
00:14:52,343 --> 00:14:55,103
Also, I have a palate like a granny. I'm not a picky eater.

441
00:14:55,343 --> 00:14:56,942
- That's another reason.
- Do you enjoy all kinds of food?

442
00:14:56,943 --> 00:14:57,972
- Granny Chung?
- Yes.

443
00:14:57,973 --> 00:15:01,282
- Do you like cilantro?
- I really like it.

444
00:15:01,283 --> 00:15:03,413
- Do you eat beef omasum too?
- Yes, I like it.

445
00:15:03,513 --> 00:15:04,613
- She likes all kinds of food.
- What about ox blood?

446
00:15:04,783 --> 00:15:06,052
- I like it.
- Shin Young, you're talking...

447
00:15:06,053 --> 00:15:07,383
about the food you had yesterday.

448
00:15:07,923 --> 00:15:09,122
What she ate yesterday.

449
00:15:09,123 --> 00:15:11,153
- I ate them this morning.
- Nurungji and beef omasum...

450
00:15:11,323 --> 00:15:14,623
- You eat beef omasum for breakfast?
- Beef omasum for breakfast?

451
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,592
- You're craving it, right?
- Next up is...

452
00:15:18,593 --> 00:15:21,562
So Hye. Her nickname is Make Me So Hye?

453
00:15:21,563 --> 00:15:23,372
- Make Me So Hye?
- Make Me So Hye?

454
00:15:23,373 --> 00:15:24,502
Shall we show them?

455
00:15:24,503 --> 00:15:26,603
- One, two, three, four.
- One, two, three, four.

456
00:15:27,043 --> 00:15:29,042
(Make me sweat)

457
00:15:29,043 --> 00:15:31,013
(Make me hotter)

458
00:15:31,213 --> 00:15:33,143
- Make me sweat - Make me sweat

459
00:15:33,283 --> 00:15:35,213
- Make me hotter - I don't know what that means.

460
00:15:35,913 --> 00:15:36,913
It's a little bit...

461
00:15:36,914 --> 00:15:38,853
Guys, don't keep the joke to yourselves.

462
00:15:38,983 --> 00:15:41,253
- Let us in on the laugh!
- Tell us what it means.

463
00:15:41,323 --> 00:15:43,893
- Are you guys freezing us out?
- Make me sweat

464
00:15:44,053 --> 00:15:45,352
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

465
00:15:45,353 --> 00:15:48,163
- They became mean after ten years.
- You thought we wouldn't notice?

466
00:15:48,363 --> 00:15:49,363
There's this song...

467
00:15:49,364 --> 00:15:50,432
