00:23:50,713 --> 00:23:52,042
- from normal to bright ones.
- Exactly.

713
00:23:52,043 --> 00:23:55,242
I adore Men on a Mission and was on the show the most.

714
00:23:55,243 --> 00:23:57,813
So I came with the determination to do well.

715
00:23:58,113 --> 00:23:59,853
- Nice.
- That's good.

716
00:24:00,253 --> 00:24:01,982
- Our transfer students...
- Yes?

717
00:24:01,983 --> 00:24:05,052
wrote their team after their nicknames.

718
00:24:05,053 --> 00:24:06,392
Give them a round of applause. I.O.I.

719
00:24:06,393 --> 00:24:07,423
I.O.I.

720
00:24:07,923 --> 00:24:09,363
That's right.

721
00:24:09,493 --> 00:24:12,333
- I.O.I.
- They have reunited.

722
00:24:12,593 --> 00:24:15,562
Unbelievable!

723
00:24:15,563 --> 00:24:16,633
- It...
- He gave me a heart attack.

724
00:24:16,773 --> 00:24:18,002
Is it your buzzword?

725
00:24:18,003 --> 00:24:19,743
- He used the moves from "PICK ME."
- "PICK ME?"

726
00:24:20,003 --> 00:24:21,742
(Embarrassed)

727
00:24:21,743 --> 00:24:24,572
- Here's why it's unbelievable.
- Okay.

728
00:24:24,573 --> 00:24:26,713
They left a strong impression,

729
00:24:27,043 --> 00:24:28,243
but guess how long they were active.

730
00:24:28,813 --> 00:24:30,012
- I.O.I?
- Yes.

731
00:24:30,013 --> 00:24:32,182
- Three years?
- At least two or three years.

732
00:24:32,183 --> 00:24:33,783
- For less than a year.
- Really?

733
00:24:33,853 --> 00:24:35,682
- It was that short?
- According to data,

734
00:24:35,683 --> 00:24:36,793
it was about ten months.

735
00:24:36,993 --> 00:24:38,122
- It's the strong impression.
- A comeback in ten years...

736
00:24:38,123 --> 00:24:39,222
after ten months of promotion?

737
00:24:39,223 --> 00:24:40,322
Because of the strong impression,

738
00:24:40,323 --> 00:24:41,662
it feels like they were active for several years.

739
00:24:41,663 --> 00:24:42,932
- For three years at least.
- Aren't I right?

740
00:24:42,933 --> 00:24:44,193
- Yes.
- You are.

741
00:24:44,263 --> 00:24:45,493
Ten months, ten years!

742
00:24:45,563 --> 00:24:46,962
- We...
- Was it less than a year?

743
00:24:46,963 --> 00:24:49,133
had the shortest promotion among all the seasons.

744
00:24:49,203 --> 00:24:51,202
Overall, it's ten months. But to be nitpicky,

745
00:24:51,203 --> 00:24:53,102
- it was only about 8 to 9 months.
- Is that so?

746
00:24:53,103 --> 00:24:55,002
- It wasn't ten full months.
- Some members weren't with us.

747
00:24:55,003 --> 00:24:56,513
So I have a few regrets about it.

748
00:24:56,673 --> 00:24:57,772
- True.
- Totally.

749
00:24:57,773 --> 00:24:59,242
We didn't have a fandom name back then.

750
00:24:59,243 --> 00:25:01,683
One was made this time.

751
00:25:01,713 --> 00:25:02,912
- But...
- This time?

752
00:25:02,913 --> 00:25:03,913
- Yes.
- Yes, this time.

753
00:25:03,914 --> 00:25:07,182
Why was the promotion so short ten years ago?

754
00:25:07,183 --> 00:25:08,222
- Exactly.
- For real.

755
00:25:08,223 --> 00:25:10,822
- We regret it.
- Actually, we were the beginning.

756
00:25:10,823 --> 00:25:12,622
- The first season.
- We were the beginning...

757
00:25:12,623 --> 00:25:14,492
- of that kind of audition show.
- Right.

758
00:25:14,493 --> 00:25:17,262
Nobody, including us and the production team,

759
00:25:17,263 --> 00:25:19,593
knew it'd be such a big hit.

760
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:22,762
We didn't leave when we were gaining popularity...

761
00:25:22,763 --> 00:25:24,833
but we left when we were about to gain it.

762
00:25:24,903 --> 00:25:27,702
- That's why we're full of regrets.
- Yes.

763
00:25:27,703 --> 00:25:31,412
I heard the contracts of audition shows got longer...

764
00:25:31,413 --> 00:25:33,142
- Because of the success.
- after your show.

765
00:25:33,143 --> 00:25:34,442
- Two years?
- Yes, two years.

766
00:25:34,443 --> 00:25:35,642
- Two years each?
- They had fandom names,

767
00:25:35,643 --> 00:25:37,752
big concerts, and such, so we were jealous.

768
00:25:37,753 --> 00:25:39,482
- Exactly.
- You made it all happen.

769
00:25:39,483 --> 00:25:40,782
- Yes.
- They started...

770
00:25:40,783 --> 00:25:42,352
- the audition-show trend in Korea.
- You're right.

771
00:25:42,353 --> 00:25:43,693
- Totally.
- Right?

772
00:25:43,853 --> 00:25:46,493
What I still remember to this day is...

773
00:25:46,623 --> 00:25:48,823
Didn't you cry buckets back then?

774
00:25:48,893 --> 00:25:50,732
- We did.
- Totally.

775
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:52,062
Doesn't Yoo Jung cry a lot?

776
00:25:52,063 --> 00:25:53,063
- I...
- Yoo Jung cries easily.

777
00:25:53,064 --> 00:25:54,133
- Always.
- Yoo Jung.

778
00:25:54,763 --> 00:25:59,173
(I.O.I's Tear Fairy cried even when graduating from Brother School.)

779
00:25:59,673 --> 00:26:01,572
(What happened at the last concert)

780
00:26:01,573 --> 00:26:03,772
- At our last concert, - Yes.

781
00:26:03,773 --> 00:26:05,942
- I had a severe sty.
- A sty?

782
00:26:05,943 --> 00:26:08,642
Yes. I used to sleep anywhere...

783
00:26:08,643 --> 00:26:11,113
when I was tired back then.

784
00:26:11,153 --> 00:26:12,682
I slept on my stomach...

785
00:26:12,683 --> 00:26:14,922
- on our team house's heated floor.
- I see.

786
00:26:14,923 --> 00:26:17,523
The next morning, I couldn't recognize myself in the mirror.

787
00:26:18,623 --> 00:26:21,122
- I couldn't. I was all puffed up.
- Was it someone else?

788
00:26:21,123 --> 00:26:22,362
- The puffiness?
- My face was all puffy.

789
00:26:22,363 --> 00:26:24,032
- Was it from crying?
- That was how much I cried.

790
00:26:24,033 --> 00:26:27,233
Didn't Chungha suggest making an I.O.I Day...

791
00:26:27,703 --> 00:26:29,133
every year?

792
00:26:29,403 --> 00:26:33,743
(Question: What's my last wish for I.O.I?)

793
00:26:34,043 --> 00:26:38,743
(Let's meet up at least once a year no matter what!)

794
00:26:39,143 --> 00:26:43,583
(I.O.I promised to set a date and meet up.)

795
00:26:43,913 --> 00:26:44,953
- You did, right?
- Yes.

796
00:26:45,413 --> 00:26:48,153
It wasn't just once a year. In little groups...

797
00:26:48,183 --> 00:26:50,422
We texted each other on days off...

798
00:26:50,423 --> 00:26:51,652
- and met up.
- Yes.

799
00:26:51,653 --> 00:26:53,362
- It was in groups of 2 or 3.
- Even 4.

800
00:26:53,363 --> 00:26:56,092
When someone's work was over, we'd ask them to come over.

801
00:26:56,093 --> 00:26:57,463
We met up quite often.

802
00:26:57,663 --> 00:27:00,263
Initially, I.O.I promised...

803
00:27:00,703 --> 00:27:02,302
to reunite after...

804
00:27:02,303 --> 00:27:03,832
- five years.
- Correct.

805
00:27:03,833 --> 00:27:05,602
But the reunion took ten years.

806
00:27:05,603 --> 00:27:07,372
Why did it get pushed back?

807
00:27:07,373 --> 00:27:09,002
We kept trying to reunite.

808
00:27:09,003 --> 00:27:11,142
But with different situations...

809
00:27:11,143 --> 00:27:12,442
and solo promotions,

810
00:27:12,443 --> 00:27:13,742
- it was tough.
- You're all in different companies.

811
00:27:13,743 --> 00:27:15,412
- Yes.
- It's not easy at all.

812
00:27:15,413 --> 00:27:16,652
Some were in groups as well.

813
00:27:16,653 --> 00:27:20,052
After experiencing trial and error,

814
00:27:20,053 --> 00:27:22,252
we finally understood...

815
00:27:22,253 --> 00:27:25,622
how much time was needed to plan it all out.

816
00:27:25,623 --> 00:27:28,492
And so, we worked things out.

817
00:27:28,493 --> 00:27:29,722
- In ten years.
- Yes.

818
00:27:29,723 --> 00:27:33,862
Which member pushed the reunion the most?

819
00:27:33,863 --> 00:27:35,803
- Chungha.
- Chungha.

820
00:27:35,903 --> 00:27:37,133
- Is that so?
- Yes.

821
00:27:37,233 --> 00:27:40,973
I would go perform at events as a solo artist...

822
00:27:41,043 --> 00:27:44,972
and would spot I.O.I's cheering stick.

823
00:27:44,973 --> 00:27:46,912
- The cheering stick?
- Yes.

824
00:27:46,913 --> 00:27:49,912
After the performance, I'd always get asked...

825
00:27:49,913 --> 00:27:51,612
by some fans...

826
00:27:51,613 --> 00:27:55,052
to sign our debut album or unit album.

827
00:27:55,053 --> 00:27:57,623
I would always happily sign them.

828
00:27:57,723 --> 00:28:00,992
I realized many fans were waiting for us.

829
00:28:00,993 --> 00:28:05,362
We always brought up our tenth debut anniversary.

830
00:28:05,363 --> 00:28:07,462
I saw the need...

831
00:28:07,463 --> 00:28:10,102
to contact everyone around this time of the year, so I did.

832
00:28:10,103 --> 00:28:11,973
Rumor had it that...

833
00:28:12,133 --> 00:28:14,603
because Wanna One was reuniting,

834
00:28:15,443 --> 00:28:17,142
I.O.I would too.

835
00:28:17,143 --> 00:28:18,172
Oh, my.

836
00:28:18,173 --> 00:28:19,773
- Wanna One...
- Actually, we were first.

837
00:28:20,143 --> 00:28:22,242
My best friend is in that group.

838
00:28:22,243 --> 00:28:24,382
- Dae Hwi is in Wanna One.
- Who? Dae Hwi.

839
00:28:24,383 --> 00:28:26,823
Let me tell him...

840
00:28:26,923 --> 00:28:28,283
- with a heart.
- Okay.

841
00:28:28,453 --> 00:28:29,753
We were first.

842
00:28:31,093 --> 00:28:33,692
- So you were first.
- You have my respect and love.

843
00:28:33,693 --> 00:28:35,292
Congratulations on reuniting.

844
00:28:35,293 --> 00:28:36,562
But we're about...

845
00:28:36,563 --> 00:28:37,832
- to release an album.
- Right.

846
00:28:37,833 --> 00:28:39,332
Since it's...

847
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:42,032
a meaningful comeback after a full ten years...

848
00:28:42,033 --> 00:28:44,102
- You were first?
- Yes, we were first.

849
00:28:44,103 --> 00:28:45,802
- I feel slightly...
- The originator.

850
00:28:45,803 --> 00:28:46,972
- Originator.
- Slightly bad.

851
00:28:46,973 --> 00:28:48,872
I feel slightly bad, but let us have...

852
00:28:48,873 --> 00:28:50,043
- the attention.
- Yes, Na Young?

853
00:28:50,113 --> 00:28:52,442
We brought it up since...

854
00:28:52,443 --> 00:28:54,342
- a year ago.
- True.

855
00:28:54,343 --> 00:28:56,612
Do you have evidence of that talk from a year ago?

856
00:28:56,613 --> 00:28:58,612
- We need proof to submit.
- Our texts.

857
00:28:58,613 --> 00:29:00,352
- Don't you have a group chat?
- We do.

858
00:29:00,353 --> 00:29:01,922
- I'm the clerk.
- Yes?

859
00:29:01,923 --> 00:29:03,752
We have records of our meetings from a year ago.

860
00:29:03,753 --> 00:29:04,792
I.O.I has evidence.

861
00:29:04,793 --> 00:29:06,192
- Are you the clerk?
- They'd accept it.

862
00:29:06,193 --> 00:29:08,122
- I was the clerk.
- They are indeed originators.

863
00:29:08,123 --> 00:29:09,722
- Of course they'd have proof.
- Yes.

864
00:29:09,723 --> 00:29:11,632
Who talks the most and is the loudest among you guys?

865
00:29:11,633 --> 00:29:13,702
- She's not here with us.
- She's not?

866
00:29:13,703 --> 00:29:15,302
- Se Jeong.
- Right.

867
00:29:15,303 --> 00:29:17,802
- I can't agree more.
- Se Jeong would send us...

868
00:29:17,803 --> 00:29:19,832
a long text when she got home after every practice...

869
00:29:19,833 --> 00:29:21,442
even though we were together the whole day.

870
00:29:21,443 --> 00:29:23,042
"Guys, I'm so happy."

871
00:29:23,043 --> 00:29:24,372
- "Today, this happened."
- An emotional text.

872
00:29:24,373 --> 00:29:25,542
She'd send a thank-you text...

873
00:29:25,543 --> 00:29:27,042
- to the group chat.
- Yes.

874
00:29:27,043 --> 00:29:29,642
I heard that you guys got together...

875
00:29:29,643 --> 00:29:31,352
and did the choreography again,

876
00:29:31,353 --> 00:29:32,812
and you were surprised...

877
00:29:32,813 --> 00:29:35,122
and so was your instructor, Bae Yoon Jung.

878
00:29:35,123 --> 00:29:36,123
- Yes.
- Really?

879
00:29:36,124 --> 00:29:37,392
Production crew, please show us.

880
00:29:37,393 --> 00:29:38,393
- Really?
- Why?

881
00:29:38,394 --> 00:29:41,563
(I.O.I got together and shot a short-form video of "Pick Me.")

882
00:29:41,693 --> 00:29:42,923
It's recent.

883
00:29:44,593 --> 00:29:47,162
- It's ten years later.
- Gosh.

884
00:29:47,163 --> 00:29:48,232
- It's been so long.
- Are they dancing...

885
00:29:48,233 --> 00:29:49,262
in front of the mirror?

886
00:29:49,263 --> 00:29:50,332
- Yes.
- I know.

887
00:29:50,333 --> 00:29:52,032
- You can't tell.
- That's right.

888
00:29:52,033 --> 00:29:54,472
- Is that even before the practice?
- Yes.

889
00:29:54,473 --> 00:29:57,143
They have the memory from ten years back.

890
00:30:02,343 --> 00:30:07,883
(Their bright energy is the same from 10 years back.)

891
00:30:08,123 --> 00:30:09,452
(Amazed)

892
00:30:09,453 --> 00:30:11,692
- That's amazing.
- Even without practicing,

893
00:30:11,693 --> 00:30:13,152
- they can still...
- Of course.

894
00:30:13,153 --> 00:30:14,762
Your body remembers it, right?

895
00:30:14,763 --> 00:30:16,462
- I think so.
- I think so.

896
00:30:16,463 --> 00:30:19,832
Especially with So Hye, what did she say to you?

897
00:30:19,833 --> 00:30:21,032
She wrote a comment.

898
00:30:21,033 --> 00:30:22,462
"You guys are amazing."

899
00:30:22,463 --> 00:30:23,472
- "You guys are amazing."
- She gave us...

900
00:30:23,473 --> 00:30:25,132
- a thumbs up.
- Really?

901
00:30:25,133 --> 00:30:27,572
You guys got scolded a lot by her, right?

902
00:30:27,573 --> 00:30:29,202
- So Hye, especially.
- She scolds a lot.

903
00:30:29,203 --> 00:30:30,412
- We did.
- Yes.

904
00:30:30,413 --> 00:30:34,383
We will show you a much improved version of ourselves, ma'am.

905
00:30:36,283 --> 00:30:39,582
- This is Make Me So Hye.
- Yes.

906
00:30:39,583 --> 00:30:40,922
Make Me So Hye.

907
00:30:40,923 --> 00:30:44,622
You guys spent such a short time together and had to part.

908
00:30:44,623 --> 00:30:46,292
Was there anything...

909
00:30:46,293 --> 00:30:48,922
you really wanted to do when you get back together?

910
00:30:48,923 --> 00:30:52,162
What we all mentioned was a concert.

911
00:30:52,163 --> 00:30:53,332
- Yes.
- A full independent concert.

912
00:30:53,333 --> 00:30:56,502
So, we're starting from Seoul,

913
00:30:56,503 --> 00:30:58,503
and we're going on our first tour abroad.

914
00:30:59,233 --> 00:31:02,842
We're really thrilled and excited to have the chance...

915
00:31:02,843 --> 00:31:05,173
to connect with our fans.

916
00:31:05,543 --> 00:31:07,243
So, in Seoul,

917
00:31:07,513 --> 00:31:10,352
we will be having our concert from May 29th to May 31st,

918
00:31:10,353 --> 00:31:11,512
a total of three days.

919
00:31:11,513 --> 00:31:12,513
She has changed a lot.

920
00:31:12,514 --> 00:31:13,922
We will be having our concert,

921
00:31:13,923 --> 00:31:15,452
so please give us lots of love.

922
00:31:15,453 --> 00:31:17,253
It's going to be a really special performance.

923
00:31:17,593 --> 00:31:19,493
This is going to be the last chance to see us,

924
00:31:19,853 --> 00:31:23,332
- so please don't miss this chance.
- That's good.

925
00:31:23,333 --> 00:31:24,492
- That's right.
- Yes.

926
00:31:24,493 --> 00:31:27,932
You won't be able to keep performing together,

927
00:31:27,933 --> 00:31:29,132
- so it may be the last time.
- Yes.

928
00:31:29,133 --> 00:31:30,232
- That's right.
- You're right.

929
00:31:30,233 --> 00:31:31,602
The song that So Mi wrote...

930
00:31:31,603 --> 00:31:32,603
- is the title song?
- Yes.

931
00:31:32,604 --> 00:31:34,872
- Two songs.
- You wrote and composed them?

932
00:31:34,873 --> 00:31:36,972
- Yes.
- Gosh, that's great.

933
00:31:36,973 --> 00:31:39,242
- What's the title song?
- I wrote the lyrics for that,

934
00:31:39,243 --> 00:31:42,042
and I composed the first track on the album.

935
00:31:42,043 --> 00:31:43,483
When you heard the song,

936
00:31:43,813 --> 00:31:45,682
you may have heard that...

937
00:31:45,683 --> 00:31:47,222
- So Mi wrote the song, - Sure.

938
00:31:47,223 --> 00:31:49,422
or you may not have known about it,

939
00:31:49,423 --> 00:31:51,452
like a blind test.

940
00:31:51,453 --> 00:31:52,722
You knew about it, right?

941
00:31:52,723 --> 00:31:55,922
We knew about it, but at that time,

942
00:31:55,923 --> 00:31:59,332
we were searching for the right song and were exhausted,

943
00:31:59,333 --> 00:32:01,832
and we didn't know what to do. But then, So Mi said,

944
00:32:01,833 --> 00:32:03,502
"You guys, what about this?"

945
00:32:03,503 --> 00:32:05,732
She just casually played it for us,

946
00:32:05,733 --> 00:32:08,242
but we all liked it. That's how it went.

947
00:32:08,243 --> 00:32:09,302
- That was So Mi's title song?
- Yes, the title song.

948
00:32:09,303 --> 00:32:12,643
And a few days later, it kept playing in my head,

949
00:32:12,973 --> 00:32:14,082
and I was singing along.

950
00:32:14,083 --> 00:32:16,143
Are you sure it wasn't So Mi singing it next to you?

951
00:32:16,953 --> 00:32:18,682
- Next to you.
- Gaslighting them.

952
00:32:18,683 --> 00:32:19,683
Force-feeding it?

953
00:32:20,483 --> 00:32:21,822
- It was gaslighting.
- That was great.

954
00:32:21,823 --> 00:32:23,753
- Subtly.
- That was a great comment.

955
00:32:24,553 --> 00:32:26,352
It was very catchy.

956
00:32:26,353 --> 00:32:27,462
It's catchy?

957
00:32:27,463 --> 00:32:29,022
It needs to be catchy to sing along.

958
00:32:29,023 --> 00:32:30,732
- Let's not just talk about it.
- Yes.

