1449
00:50:52,763 --> 00:50:53,962
(The Tear Fairy bursts into tears again.)

1450
00:50:53,963 --> 00:50:56,362
- You're unbelievable.
- Right.

1451
00:50:56,363 --> 00:50:57,462
(Thud)

1452
00:50:57,463 --> 00:51:00,002
- Thanks.
- She really needs it.

1453
00:51:00,003 --> 00:51:01,902
- Right. I said, - All of a sudden...

1454
00:51:01,903 --> 00:51:03,642
"Thank you, Chungha."

1455
00:51:03,643 --> 00:51:06,472
And she said, "Baby, don't cry."

1456
00:51:06,473 --> 00:51:08,113
She tried to appease me like this.

1457
00:51:08,383 --> 00:51:10,742
And Yeon Jung suddenly...

1458
00:51:10,743 --> 00:51:13,913
She was standing behind me, so I didn't see her there.

1459
00:51:14,053 --> 00:51:15,622
As soon as she heard, "Baby, don't cry,"

1460
00:51:15,623 --> 00:51:18,323
she said, "Hey. You have a problem. You should see a doctor."

1461
00:51:19,423 --> 00:51:21,192
She's a thinker.

1462
00:51:21,193 --> 00:51:22,222
- Yeon Jung is a T.
- She is.

1463
00:51:22,223 --> 00:51:24,122
- She's a total T.
- Yeon Jung is a thinker.

1464
00:51:24,123 --> 00:51:26,532
- She's a T.
- No, I'm actually an F.

1465
00:51:26,533 --> 00:51:27,762
I'm a feeling-type person.

1466
00:51:27,763 --> 00:51:29,503
But she cries too often.

1467
00:51:29,733 --> 00:51:31,202
You go back and forth between T and F.

1468
00:51:31,203 --> 00:51:33,472
Seeing her cry ruins my moment.

1469
00:51:33,473 --> 00:51:35,072
- Right.
- When I'm getting emotional,

1470
00:51:35,073 --> 00:51:38,142
I look at her and find out that she's wailing.

1471
00:51:38,143 --> 00:51:39,273
When it's too much...

1472
00:51:40,143 --> 00:51:41,143
- She cries a lot.
- I can't control that.

1473
00:51:41,144 --> 00:51:42,442
I feel like, "You have a problem."

1474
00:51:42,443 --> 00:51:43,912
Yoo Jung, if you hear my sad story,

1475
00:51:43,913 --> 00:51:45,753
you'll need to take a year off.

1476
00:51:45,983 --> 00:51:47,482
- No, Sang Min...
- When you need...

1477
00:51:47,483 --> 00:51:48,882
- Sang Min.
- someone to cry for you, call me.

1478
00:51:48,883 --> 00:51:50,522
- You need to take a year off.
- What?

1479
00:51:50,523 --> 00:51:51,892
(Lee Sang Min's real name was Lee Baby.)

1480
00:51:51,893 --> 00:51:53,293
(He lived with the name for 2 years as his dad could not be reached.)

1481
00:51:53,493 --> 00:51:56,022
Yoo Jung, I'll tell you the people...

1482
00:51:56,023 --> 00:51:58,332
you specifically shouldn't meet.

1483
00:51:58,333 --> 00:51:59,833
Lee Sang Min and Lee Soo Geun.

1484
00:51:59,963 --> 00:52:01,402
- Why me?
- People who have a lot of stories.

1485
00:52:01,403 --> 00:52:03,302
If you hear the story of Soo Geun's childhood...

1486
00:52:03,303 --> 00:52:04,303
No, that's not it.

1487
00:52:04,304 --> 00:52:05,832
You can't help but cry.

1488
00:52:05,833 --> 00:52:07,602
Because it's a story about family.

1489
00:52:07,603 --> 00:52:10,072
If Yoo Jung hears the family story, she won't just wail.

1490
00:52:10,073 --> 00:52:11,872
- She will faint.
- I'm 100 percent sure.

1491
00:52:11,873 --> 00:52:15,212
This is the last item for today's I.O.I News.

1492
00:52:15,213 --> 00:52:17,143
It's about So Mi.

1493
00:52:17,813 --> 00:52:19,652
She's called the queen of war of nerves.

1494
00:52:19,653 --> 00:52:20,782
(So Mi is the queen of war of nerves approved by Internet users.)

1495
00:52:20,783 --> 00:52:24,023
Even Internet users acknowledge it.

1496
00:52:24,123 --> 00:52:26,152
I like observing people.

1497
00:52:26,153 --> 00:52:29,422
I once reenacted a subtle war of nerves...

1498
00:52:29,423 --> 00:52:32,232
between the women there.

1499
00:52:32,233 --> 00:52:33,592
It went viral...

1500
00:52:33,593 --> 00:52:35,302
and it has now reached seven million views.

1501
00:52:35,303 --> 00:52:36,532
- That's amazing.
- Really?

1502
00:52:36,533 --> 00:52:39,702
Are you good at getting on other people's nerves?

1503
00:52:39,703 --> 00:52:41,032
I'm good at copying others.

1504
00:52:41,033 --> 00:52:42,742
So, it has reached seven million views already.

1505
00:52:42,743 --> 00:52:44,442
Now that you're back here after ten years,

1506
00:52:44,443 --> 00:52:45,512
we should make it ten million views.

1507
00:52:45,513 --> 00:52:46,913
- Let's do that.
- Shin Young.

1508
00:52:47,043 --> 00:52:48,342
All right.

1509
00:52:48,343 --> 00:52:50,443
- It sounds fun.
- I'm a little nervous.

1510
00:52:50,513 --> 00:52:51,513
Let's go.

1511
00:52:51,553 --> 00:52:54,283
Soo Geun is the MC of Korea's best music show.

1512
00:52:54,653 --> 00:52:56,352
You are going to his waiting room...

1513
00:52:56,353 --> 00:52:58,093
- to say hello to him.
- Okay.

1514
00:52:58,193 --> 00:52:59,592
Would there be a war of nerves?

1515
00:52:59,593 --> 00:53:01,322
- Of course, there would be.
- Stand by.

1516
00:53:01,323 --> 00:53:02,963
- Ten million views. Action.
- Okay.

1517
00:53:03,723 --> 00:53:04,932
(Congratulations on I.O.I's comeback after 10 years.)

1518
00:53:04,933 --> 00:53:05,933
(The war of nerves between singers)

1519
00:53:05,934 --> 00:53:07,232
This week's "Top Ten Songs..."

1520
00:53:07,233 --> 00:53:08,532
- Hello.
- "Top Ten Songs."

1521
00:53:08,533 --> 00:53:09,932
- Hello, sir.
- Hello.

1522
00:53:09,933 --> 00:53:11,003
Two, three.

1523
00:53:11,063 --> 00:53:12,902
- We're Celeb Five.
- I was surprised.

1524
00:53:12,903 --> 00:53:13,932
- Hello.
- You showed up suddenly.

1525
00:53:13,933 --> 00:53:15,572
- Hello.
- We're a team.

1526
00:53:15,573 --> 00:53:17,342
Yes, I love it! We're I.O.I.

1527
00:53:17,343 --> 00:53:19,812
- Hello.
- Did you release a new album?

1528
00:53:19,813 --> 00:53:21,642
No. It's a song released five years ago,

1529
00:53:21,643 --> 00:53:23,583
but we want to give it a try again.

1530
00:53:23,713 --> 00:53:25,382
- A song released five years ago?
- Yes.

1531
00:53:25,383 --> 00:53:27,812
We are performing a song we released ten years ago.

1532
00:53:27,813 --> 00:53:29,522
We've worked on it for a really long time,

1533
00:53:29,523 --> 00:53:30,682
and we're finally making our comeback.

1534
00:53:30,683 --> 00:53:32,192
- Let me get a lot of close-ups.
- Right.

1535
00:53:32,193 --> 00:53:33,752
(Patting her on the shoulder)

1536
00:53:33,753 --> 00:53:36,663
- It must be great.
- So Mi has gone through a lot.

1537
00:53:36,763 --> 00:53:38,092
Right, So Mi?

1538
00:53:38,093 --> 00:53:39,732
Is this a boy band?

1539
00:53:39,733 --> 00:53:41,763
(Adam Smith's Invisible Hand)

1540
00:53:42,003 --> 00:53:43,202
(After smiling for a bit)

1541
00:53:43,203 --> 00:53:45,832
- No. We just look like boys.
- Is that so?

1542
00:53:45,833 --> 00:53:47,002
We are a boy-like band. And So Mi...

1543
00:53:47,003 --> 00:53:49,242
How long has it been since Celeb Five's debut?

1544
00:53:49,243 --> 00:53:50,272
(Serious music)

1545
00:53:50,273 --> 00:53:51,843
- Celeb Five?
- Yes.

1546
00:53:53,273 --> 00:53:54,912
- We debuted in 2018.
- I see.

1547
00:53:54,913 --> 00:53:56,913
We debuted in 2016.

1548
00:53:56,983 --> 00:53:58,112
We were a little faster.

1549
00:53:58,113 --> 00:53:59,113
(The sound effect of defeat)

1550
00:53:59,153 --> 00:54:01,112
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

1551
00:54:01,113 --> 00:54:03,152
- It can happen.
- It's okay. Go ahead.

1552
00:54:03,153 --> 00:54:05,323
(The sound effect of waving dismissively)

1553
00:54:06,253 --> 00:54:07,592
- Go ahead.
- All right.

1554
00:54:07,593 --> 00:54:10,662
We're making a comeback now. Please take good care of us.

1555
00:54:10,663 --> 00:54:12,162
All right. It's nice...

1556
00:54:12,163 --> 00:54:13,562
that you came here to talk to me.

1557
00:54:13,563 --> 00:54:14,802
Of course. I should do that.

1558
00:54:14,803 --> 00:54:16,432
- We should greet you in person.
- How nice.

1559
00:54:16,433 --> 00:54:17,763
(Awkward smile)

1560
00:54:17,903 --> 00:54:20,032
- So your new album is coming out?
- Look at her face.

1561
00:54:20,033 --> 00:54:21,672
- Yes.
- Really? I had no idea.

1562
00:54:21,673 --> 00:54:23,373
- Is she ignoring her?
- I hope...

1563
00:54:24,003 --> 00:54:26,372
- things will go well for you.
- My goodness.

1564
00:54:26,373 --> 00:54:27,743
(Serious music)

1565
00:54:31,713 --> 00:54:32,752
I feel the same way.

1566
00:54:32,753 --> 00:54:35,423
(I feel the same way.)

1567
00:54:36,553 --> 00:54:39,693
(She overpowers her by saying "I feel the same way.")

1568
00:54:40,023 --> 00:54:41,052
"I feel the same way."

1569
00:54:41,053 --> 00:54:42,592
- You're really talented.
- Right.

1570
00:54:42,593 --> 00:54:43,922
- I'm sorry, but this is a room...
- Please take care of us.

1571
00:54:43,923 --> 00:54:45,293
for comedians. What brings you here?

1572
00:54:45,763 --> 00:54:46,992
- Is this a room for comedians?
- Yes.

1573
00:54:46,993 --> 00:54:48,832
- We're new comedians.
- We can do anything.

1574
00:54:48,833 --> 00:54:50,532
- Can you?
- Yes. We can do anything.

1575
00:54:50,533 --> 00:54:52,272
We should do a skit together.

1576
00:54:52,273 --> 00:54:53,632
(They finish it with a comedy skit.)

1577
00:54:53,633 --> 00:54:55,003
- They're good.
- Okay.

1578
00:54:55,103 --> 00:54:57,772
- That was great.
- So Mi is good at this.

1579
00:54:57,773 --> 00:55:00,913
(A perfect finish that made everyone laugh)

1580
00:55:01,113 --> 00:55:02,612
- Her face...
- It was over with her last line.

1581
00:55:02,613 --> 00:55:04,413
How were you feeling when she said, "I feel the same way?"

1582
00:55:04,683 --> 00:55:06,053
When she said that, honestly,

1583
00:55:06,583 --> 00:55:08,382
I almost threw my biceps at her.

1584
00:55:08,383 --> 00:55:10,653
When she said that, I was like this.

1585
00:55:10,683 --> 00:55:12,852
- Girls don't usually fight openly.
- That's true.

1586
00:55:12,853 --> 00:55:15,192
They subtly hide their emotions like this...

1587
00:55:15,193 --> 00:55:17,222
and fight with their eyes.

1588
00:55:17,223 --> 00:55:18,662
Like when you go to a beauty salon.

1589
00:55:18,663 --> 00:55:20,262
Hello, So Mi.

1590
00:55:20,263 --> 00:55:21,263
(The war of nerves between singers in a beauty salon)

1591
00:55:21,264 --> 00:55:22,833
- Hello.
- Yes.

1592
00:55:23,533 --> 00:55:25,372
I used to be a fan. A long time ago.

1593
00:55:25,373 --> 00:55:26,373
- Right.
- A long time ago?

1594
00:55:26,374 --> 00:55:29,602
Yes. I did a talent show when I was in elementary school.

1595
00:55:29,603 --> 00:55:32,472
- Really?
- Yes. I performed "Pick Me."

1596
00:55:32,473 --> 00:55:34,373
The song was really famous.

1597
00:55:34,573 --> 00:55:36,213
So, what's your name?

1598
00:55:36,943 --> 00:55:38,453
I'm Kim Shin Young!

1599
00:55:39,953 --> 00:55:41,083
It's really annoying.

1600
00:55:41,683 --> 00:55:44,422
- I got furious.
- You need to stay relaxed.

1601
00:55:44,423 --> 00:55:46,692
- You need to be relaxed.
- She's very annoying, right?

1602
00:55:46,693 --> 00:55:47,922
She's really good at it.

1603
00:55:47,923 --> 00:55:50,623
That's it for the I.O.I News.

1604
00:55:50,763 --> 00:55:52,892
They wrote their preferred partners for variety shows.

1605
00:55:52,893 --> 00:55:54,393
Na Young wrote...

1606
00:55:55,133 --> 00:55:56,433
Lee Sang Min.

1607
00:55:56,963 --> 00:55:58,002
- Thanks.
- She mentioned it.

1608
00:55:58,003 --> 00:55:59,172
We are partners.

1609
00:55:59,173 --> 00:56:00,502
We were similar like...

1610
00:56:00,503 --> 00:56:01,842
- "The Little Mermaid."
- Right. Sing "Under the Sea."

1611
00:56:01,843 --> 00:56:03,672
I feel a certain affection for him.

1612
00:56:03,673 --> 00:56:04,872
- Affection for him?
- Affection.

1613
00:56:04,873 --> 00:56:05,972
Like how people naturally favor their own.

1614
00:56:05,973 --> 00:56:07,072
- Right.
- I think so.

1615
00:56:07,073 --> 00:56:09,443
Your team name has to be Under the Sea.

1616
00:56:09,483 --> 00:56:10,812
- Under the sea - Good.

1617
00:56:10,813 --> 00:56:13,112
(Na Young and Sang Min's voices have gone to the seabed.)

1618
00:56:13,113 --> 00:56:14,853
Next is Chungha.

1619
00:56:15,753 --> 00:56:16,782
She chose Ho Dong.

1620
00:56:16,783 --> 00:56:18,523
(Chungha's preferred partner: Kang Ho Dong)

1621
00:56:18,793 --> 00:56:20,392
I don't want to spoil the mood,

1622
00:56:20,393 --> 00:56:22,963
but honestly, I chose him because nobody else did.

1623
00:56:24,093 --> 00:56:25,392
- Seriously?
- Chungha is so nice.

1624
00:56:25,393 --> 00:56:27,032
- Really?
- Out of pity?

1625
00:56:27,033 --> 00:56:28,862
- No one chose him?
- That's so sad.

1626
00:56:28,863 --> 00:56:31,362
- Chungha, you annoyed me well.
- No.

1627
00:56:31,363 --> 00:56:33,172
- Chungha is really...
- That's what TV shows are like now.

1628
00:56:33,173 --> 00:56:35,402
- That's not it.
- That's what young people do now.

1629
00:56:35,403 --> 00:56:37,102
You are even better than So Mi.

1630
00:56:37,103 --> 00:56:40,373
No. Actually, I was glad. Here's why.

1631
00:56:41,143 --> 00:56:42,412
Listen. I'm serious.

1632
00:56:42,413 --> 00:56:43,982
- Chungha.
- Because no one chose me?

1633
00:56:43,983 --> 00:56:45,113
- Were you glad?
- No.

1634
00:56:45,213 --> 00:56:46,582
I thought it was fate.

1635
00:56:46,583 --> 00:56:48,452
Because ten years ago,

1636
00:56:48,453 --> 00:56:49,482
Ho Dong and I were partners.

1637
00:56:49,483 --> 00:56:50,622
We played a game...

1638
00:56:50,623 --> 00:56:51,722
- where we had a physical fight.
- Right.

1639
00:56:51,723 --> 00:56:53,153
We were partners back then.

1640
00:56:53,293 --> 00:56:54,392
You don't remember it, do you?

1641
00:56:54,393 --> 00:56:55,592
Of course, I remember.

1642
00:56:55,593 --> 00:56:56,593
We had a pillow battle.

1643
00:56:56,594 --> 00:56:58,762
- Right.
- We played pillow games together.

1644
00:56:58,763 --> 00:57:00,892
So I think it's our destiny...

1645
00:57:00,893 --> 00:57:02,663
that we've become partners again.

1646
00:57:03,233 --> 00:57:04,563
We are fated partners.

1647
00:57:04,733 --> 00:57:06,302
All right. Chungha chose Ho Dong.

1648
00:57:06,303 --> 00:57:08,173
Thanks, Chungha.

1649
00:57:08,273 --> 00:57:09,902
- It's good to see you again.
- Make Me So Hye.

1650
00:57:09,903 --> 00:57:12,272
Make Me So Hye chose Soo Geun.

1651
00:57:12,273 --> 00:57:14,142
- Soo Geun.
- She chose Soo Geun.

1652
00:57:14,143 --> 00:57:15,812
Do you remember it, Soo Geun?

1653
00:57:15,813 --> 00:57:16,912
That...

1654
00:57:16,913 --> 00:57:18,552
His reaction was cold. He's like, "What?"

1655
00:57:18,553 --> 00:57:19,712
Tell me what it is.

1656
00:57:19,713 --> 00:57:20,882
- Do you...
- What is it?

1657
00:57:20,883 --> 00:57:22,953
- "Do you remember me?"
- still have the gift I gave you?

1658
00:57:23,123 --> 00:57:24,222
- What?
- Wait.

1659
00:57:24,223 --> 00:57:25,652
- You should wait.
- Don't say it.

1660
00:57:25,653 --> 00:57:27,422
- Wait. Don't say what it is.
- Was it a gift?

1661
00:57:27,423 --> 00:57:28,622
- What was it?
- A gift?

1662
00:57:28,623 --> 00:57:30,462
- I know what it is.
- One, two, three.

1663
00:57:30,463 --> 00:57:31,733
A gift certificate.

1664
00:57:31,833 --> 00:57:32,863
(Shocked)

1665
00:57:33,233 --> 00:57:34,463
- Really?
- Was that it?

1666
00:57:34,793 --> 00:57:35,833
Wrong!

1667
00:57:36,203 --> 00:57:37,402
Didn't you give me a gift certificate?

1668
00:57:37,403 --> 00:57:39,073
- No.
- A doll.

1669
00:57:39,403 --> 00:57:41,102
- That's right.
- Right? I knew it.

1670
00:57:41,103 --> 00:57:42,442
Then who gave you a gift certificate?

1671
00:57:42,443 --> 00:57:44,202
That was just a joke.

1672
00:57:44,203 --> 00:57:46,343
So Hye gave me a doll back then.

1673
00:57:46,713 --> 00:57:48,642
It wasn't just me. She gave one to each of us.

1674
00:57:48,643 --> 00:57:50,513
- What kind of doll was it?
- What?

1675
00:57:50,743 --> 00:57:51,752
What doll?

1676
00:57:51,753 --> 00:57:53,582
You know the one that makes you sick when pricked with a needle.

1677
00:57:53,583 --> 00:57:55,222
That's scary.

1678
00:57:55,223 --> 00:57:56,852
- That's a voodoo doll.
- A voodoo doll?

1679
00:57:56,853 --> 00:57:58,623
- She gave you a voodoo doll?
- A voodoo doll.

1680
00:57:58,693 --> 00:58:01,022
What kind of doll was it? Just tell me.

1681
00:58:01,023 --> 00:58:02,593
- A voodoo doll.
- A voodoo doll.

1682
00:58:02,763 --> 00:58:05,492
I gave you two penguin dolls.

1683
00:58:05,493 --> 00:58:06,733
For my kids?

1684
00:58:06,893 --> 00:58:08,803
That's right. They were for my kids.

1685
00:58:08,963 --> 00:58:11,632
(Soo Geun has...)

1686
00:58:11,633 --> 00:58:16,273
(2 animals.)

1687
00:58:17,003 --> 00:58:19,443
(I'm sorry!)

1688
00:58:19,843 --> 00:58:22,142
(That's how the 2 penguins went to Soo Geun's 2 children.)

1689
00:58:22,143 --> 00:58:25,353
The eldest one is becoming an adult next year.

1690
00:58:26,453 --> 00:58:28,083
It feels so strange.

1691
00:58:28,113 --> 00:58:29,982
I see. I remember that.

1692
00:58:29,983 --> 00:58:31,622
- Next is Yeon Jung.
- Yes.

1693
00:58:31,623 --> 00:58:33,023
